  "doc_id": "51816",
  "text": "PV is a clonal hematologic disorder, characterized by unwarranted red blood cell production. Patients have increased risks of thrombosis, myelofibrosis, and secondary acute myeloid leukemia [CITATION_1] . The JAK2 V617F mutation which results in cytokine-independent growth of hematopoietic cells presents in about 95% patients with PV [CITATION_2] . To the best of our knowledge, this is the first report of PV diagnosed in an unrelated donor after PBSC donation. The asymptomatic mutation was present before G-CSF administration.",
